> 
> Sorry, I missed it during my first review. I think this value should be false and not true. Am I wrong?

In math, any of an empty set is true...

Let's change this to:

```js
_.forEach(jobList, function(job) {
  aggregateJobPlatform(repoName, job, platformData);
}
```

When I test this locally, I'm not getting the same response from the old code as the new.  We need to handle the case where the ``prop`` does not exist in the ``locationSearch``:

old:

    Object { repo: "mozilla-inbound" }

new:

    Object { repo: "mozilla-inbound", revision: undefined, author: undefined, fromchange: undefined, tochange: undefined, startdate: undefined, enddate: undefined, nojobs: undefined }

This is pre-existing (even before the recent #3570 change), however it looks like `selectJobCanceller` is never set back to `null` after the requests completes. 

However, looking at the MDN examples I think it should be fine to re-use the same `AbortController()` instance each time (presuming the `.abort()` works if used multiple times) - which means we can remove the conditional entirely. eg:

```js
const selectJobController = new AbortController();

const selectJob = function (job) {
  // ...
  if (job.id) {
    // Cancel any in-progress fetch requests.
    selectJobController.abort();
    $scope.job_detail_loading = true;
    // ...
};

$rootScope.$on(thEvents.clearSelectedJob, function () {
  // Cancel any in-progress fetch requests.
  selectJobController.abort();
});
```

I've also replaced `window.AbortController` with `AbortController` in that example. If the older ESLint version we're using errors (because its list of known browser globals is out of date), then lets add an eslint ignore line with a TODO to remove it once we're on a newer version :-)

I agree that Admin UI will benefit from translation on this one, so we should do it. I'm just concerned wondering where is the best place to put, perhaps just directly in admin model view:

```Python
# invenio_pidstore/admin.py
class PersistentIdentifierModelView(ModelView):
    form_choices = {
        'status': ((PIDStatus.NEW, _('New')),
                      (PIDStatus.RESERVED, _('Reserved')), ...)
    }
```
I'm not even sure whether the ordered listing of of PIDStatus is going to be reusable anyway.

